The federal government has commiserated with the Government and People of Ghana over the loss of more than 50 lives resulting from a head-on collission involving two public transport buses. The accident occurred in the early hours of Friday. The Minister of Foreign Affairs, Mr Geoffrey Onyeama, said this in a statement by the ministry’s spokesperson, Mr George Edokpa, on Friday in Abuja. According to him, the accident, which led to the injury of several others, occurred on the Kintampo Techiman Road, Bono East Region, Ghana. The minister commended the emergency services for their efforts in rescuing passengers trapped in the vehicles. He offered Nigeria’s fervent prayers for the quick recovery of those injured, condoled those that lost loved ones and convened Nigeria’s solidarity in their time of grief. (NAN).